Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: K Road Power is an independent power producer that develops, owns and operates utility-scale renewable energy projects with a focus on building photovoltaic solar facilities to generate clean and reliable energy. K Road Power’s predecessor company was founded in 2002 as a vehicle to help recapitalize and restructure troubled US power companies following the power market crash of 2001, K Road affiliates oversaw the purchase of nearly 3,000 MW of natural gas and oil fired generating capacity.  In 2008 the company turned its sights exclusively to the renewable power sector and power infrastructure related to building a clean, sustainable energy future for the United States. In August of 2011, Barclays Natural Resource Investments ("BNRI"), a division of Barclays Capital, focused on natural resource investment opportunities made a significant investment in K Road. With the support of a strong financial partner, K Road is well positioned to pursue an advanced pipeline of high-viability development projects and acquisitions. Today, the firm has nine fully permitted utility scale power projects in four regions around the United States totaling over 900 MWs, of these 25 MWs are in operation, 320 MWs are entering the construction phase and expected to be completed by the end of 2013 and the balance is completing final stages of development.  In addition, the firm has a large number of prospective projects at various stages of development, totaling an additional 2,000 MWs. Headquartered in New York City, K Road has offices in San Francisco and Shanghai.  K Road promotes sustainable, renewable energy development and the principles of environmental and social responsibility with a focus on the creation of long-term shareholder value.

Description: The Ledger family of publications is your indispensable source of news and information about Central Florida's Polk County.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: The history of The Ledger dates to Aug. 22, 1924, when Sam Farabee started The Lakeland Evening Ledger under the Ledger Publishing Co. Three years later, the Lakeland Ledger Publishing Co. bought one of its competitors, The Star-Telegram, which continued as a morning newspaper. A year later, when the owners figured out that running two papers from one plant wasn't profitable, they merged the newspapers to form The Lakeland Ledger and Star-Telegram. In 1941, the name was shortened to The Lakeland Ledger. It was shortened further to The Ledger in 1967. Several owners controlled the newspaper until 1970, when The New York Times Co. purchased it, newspapers in Ocala and Gainesville, and other media interests. It was sold again in January 2012, when Daytona Beach-based Halifax Media Group bought it and the other newspapers in The New York Times Regional Newspaper Group chain. The newspaper went through many changes through the years, returning to a morning edition in April 1979. In 1998 it started its website, www.theledger.com – the same year it moved into its new building on Lime Street in Lakeland. Two years after moving into the new building The Ledger added color to all of its section fronts, thanks to increased capacity on two printing presses. It now uses those presses to print products for a variety of outside sources, including The New York Times and the Wall Street Journal. Since then, the newspaper has purchased its competition to the east, the News Chief, which now falls under the Ledger Media Group umbrella along with print products such as Inside Polk magazine. It also owns a host of newspaper-related web sites, such as TimeoutPolk.com, Polkpreps.com, PoliticsinPolk.com, and its newest, Polkcollegesports.com. The Ledger has a long history of award-winning journalism, most recently winning top state awards given by the Florida Society of News Editors and the South Florida chapter of the Society of Professional Journalists. It also has won several national awards in recent years for courtroom and breaking-news photography, and a series on the death of a middle-school student by a fellow student.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment

The company’s therapeutics offer the potential to significantly reduce the amount of drug that needs to be infused, which translates to patient and medical benefits of better efficacy, shorter infusion times, reduced immunogenicity, and greater convenience. Our lead program is for Pompe Disease but we are also applying our IGF2 technology to other LSDs to improve drug targeting and efficacy. We have also created a more stable enzyme which has the potential to be a superior ERT for Gaucher Disease.

El Paseo Hospitality Funding, LP a federally approved USCIS Regional Center based in Irvine, CA is providing $11 million in EB-5 investor capital. West River Inc. was selected by the City of Palm Desert via an extensive RFP process to develop the hotel. West River Inc. has the existing Development Agreement, Exclusive Negotiating Agreement Land Purchase Agreement and a $1.8 million dollar Transient Occupancy Tax repayment agreement. The City of Palm Desert purchased the site for $5.5 million and is contributing the land to the project for $2.2 million dollars. The hotel will be flagged as a Marriott Autograph Collection Hotel. Richfield Hospitality Inc. a Marriott approved full-service management firm will manage the hotel. The hotel will be constructed by Davis Reed Construction with bonding capacity of $500 million. Davis Reed Construction will provide a Fixed Price, Guaranteed Maximum Priced contract. The project is ready to build subject to completing final construction drawings, final architectural committee review and processing a building permit. Headquarters Regions: Tampa Bay Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Vision Computer Programming Services, Inc. has been working with Boys & Girls Clubs organizations since 1991. Vision began working with the Boys & Girls Clubs of Tampa Bay, Inc., developing a tracking system for the clubs. The tracking system was first developed in File Pro and Multiplan on 8 megahertz computers with 10 meg hard drives. The first tracking system tracked basic membership information only. As computer technology improved and software grew to better meet the demands of users, so did the Child Tracking System. In 1996 Boys & Girls Clubs of Tampa Bay reviewed all databases currently in the market and asked Vision to rewrite a new Child Tracking System using the latest technology available and to tap into the experience and insight from all levels of the organization. The result was Child Tracking System 1.0 for Windows and Microsoft Access 2.0. Over the next year, additional improvements were made and associates began to encourage Vision to market the Child Tracking System software nationally. They attended their first Area Conference in Lakeland, FL, in 1997 and their first Boys & Girls Clubs of America National Conference in Orlando, Florida, in 1998.

Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: BizGreet powers video ads that change dynamically and instantly to reach each unique viewer with a tailored message. With BizGreet the transition from broadcast advertising to narrowcast is complete: Rather than creating a single video message that is uniformly distributed to all viewers without any regard of them being part of the target audience for this message, BizGreet allows the real-time tailoring and large-scale delivery of video ads with content assembled exclusively for each viewer, dramatically increasing message relevance and effectiveness.  By personalizing video streams to each viewer based on any available CRM data, social network data, IP location or language information, BizGreet can cut inefficiencies from advertising and ensure that marketing messages are once again truly relevant to every viewer.  BizGreet ads can not only greet a viewer with their name, but also adjust the message delivered based on the viewer's past purchases, current location, age or gender - and deliver it in their preferred language. BizGreet videos can be delivered inside the Facebook canvas, played on mobile devices, hosted on any third party website with ease, or be made accessible with PURL hosting.  On the back-end, BizGreet can supply detailed information about viewer behavior - who watched their message, did they follow the call to action, did they share the video with friends. This powerful business intelligence allows BizGreet to offer unsurpassed CPA pricing, ensuring that clients only pay for success in delivering the message to the customer and the customer to the point-of-sale.

Description: Implantable Microchip for Pets with GPS Tracking.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Escape Alert is the world's first implantable chip for pets WITH GPS tracking. This product alerts pet owners if their pet has gone beyond an establisehd boundary and allow immediate tracking with GPS. Today's microchips cannot track lost pets & are of no use at all if the pet is never found. GPS collars need constant charging, are heavy & too big for small pets, have problems with reception & can strangle pets if they become tangled. Escape Alert's chip is implanted into the pet and the owner sets up a virtual boundary using proprietary software. The battery is powered "off" until activated manually to conserve energy. If the pet goes beyond the established boundary, the pet owner receives alerts via text & email. The software can be set so that others can get alerts too. Once the notifications are received, the pet owner manually powers the chip "on" thorugh the software & the pet's exact location is immediately tracked using GPS chip embedded in the microchip.
